&lt;p&gt;Valo Health is seeking an Associate Director to lead laboratory informatics and platform automation across its drug discovery organization. The role owns strategy, implementation, and operational performance across both domains, builds the scientific data infrastructure connecting bench data to Valo’s Opal Computational Platform, and leads a technical team. The ideal candidate brings deep domain expertise and a proven track record of people leadership in a fast-paced R&amp;amp;D environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Do…&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Your primary areas of responsibility will be:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own strategy, implementation, and operations across laboratory informatics systems (LIMS, ELN, SDMS, data analysis tools) and hardware automation platforms (HTS, compound management, instrument integration).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Define roadmap priorities with scientific and technical stakeholders; translate needs into actionable plans and deliver reliable solutions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with the Data Platform team to build data infrastructure, including ontologies, pipelines, and LIMS integrations; design workflow integrations that streamline operations and enable downstream AI/ML use.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Gather requirements from stakeholders to guide development across SDMS, ELN, and visualization tools; oversee user requirement specifications and UAT.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Implement data security and IP protection standards in partnership with Data Governance teams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversee data ingestion pipelines and LIMS integrations, ensuring integrity, compliance, and harmonization of legacy and current experimental data.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with scientific power users and facilities to manage vendor relationships, including contract renewals, installations, application support, and user training; oversee resource prioritization, cost monitoring, and lifecycle planning with contracts, finance, and IT.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as the senior point of expertise for informatics and automation, building strong relationships across Biology, Chemistry, DMPK, and Data Sciences.&lt;/li&gt;
