&lt;p&gt;Valo Health is seeking a Scientist I to join the Compound Management team, supporting the day-to-day operations of compound handling, registration, and distribution across its drug discovery organization. This is a hands-on laboratory role for a detail-oriented, resourceful scientist with strong experience in compound management automation and a continuous improvement mindset. The successful candidate will work cross-functionally with IVP, ADME, chemistry, and DEL technology teams to ensure compounds are accurately tracked, prepared, and delivered to support Valo’s scientific functions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Do…&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Execute compound management workflows including compound registration, weighing, stock solution reformatting, inventory curation, liquid-liquid plate transfers, and archive storage.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with IVP, ADME, chemistry, and biology teams to coordinate compound activities and deliver assay-ready plates in support of rapid DMTA cycles and HTS campaigns.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain consumable supplies; author and maintain SOPs, protocols, and inventory records to ensure data integrity, accurate audit trails, and operational continuity.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Interface with CROs and vendors for external compound inventories, purchasable compound orders, and shipments; support service contract coordination and vendor troubleshooting.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work with chemistry and DEL technology teams to curate and manage the chemical building block inventory, ensuring accurate registration, stock integrity, and alignment with program needs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design and enable new plating workflows to support IVP and ADME science teams; troubleshoot automation and software platforms and integrate novel workflows as needs evolve.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Stay current with industry trends in compound management and liquid handling; propose and build the case for adoption of new technologies and workflow improvements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You Bring... &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;BS in a scientific discipline with 8+ years of relevant laboratory experience, including a minimum of 5 years in compound management.

